        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 10:53PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1053 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Britton, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Groton, Britton, Langford, Hecla, Bath, Sunset Colony, Columbia,
Pierpont, Claremont, Newport Colony, Putney, Kidder, Lake City,
Westwood Colony, Cattail Lake, Houghton, Hillhead, Tacoma Park, Fort
Sisseton State Park, and Amherst.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Aberdeen.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
northeastern South Dakota.</instruction>
